I feel myself growing older and more mature.  I good friend of mine pointed out that he had finally figured out he was an adult and that his action were his actions.  That got me to thinking.  This weekend I got a couple of hours to ponder several things that has been on my mind.  Not that these questions have been answered but I now feel I'm on a closer path after 2 hours of reflection and meditation in the woods.

You see in my younger days I had a spot, my spot where I went to vent anger, frustation, sadness, and struggle through depression.  I went back there this weekend and it was like reliving my adolesence.  I remebered every scar on my body and every scar on my whomping tree.  My womping tree is a tree that has taken the brunt of my anger from early adolesense straight through till I began college.  I chose an old yet strong oak tree standing above the surounding forest.  This tree symbolized everything I wanted to be as a person.  Seeing it this weekend nearly brought tears as I realized just how far I've swayed from what I thought I would be.  I went to punching it to let out my pain, sorrow, and all of my saddness.  Once again painting its strong bark with the blood from my nuckles.  

The best thing I've seen in a long time was coming back up the road from my spot my nuckles red, and my parents smiling telling me that I was going to be fine without having to ask what was wrong.  It was then walking up the driveway that I knew my problems were my own and that my parents respected the fact that I am an adult.

As the chaos approaches the light in the world turns to dark.  You gather your friends and your inner strength to stand agaisnt the darkness.      You are engulfed by the darkness your soul begins to twist and turn as you shake off the pain and keep fighting.  Right as you were about to give up a beacon of light blasts through the darkness saving you.  Your sword glows with a different light reacting to the light shining through the darkness.  
     You move through the hole made from the blast of light your sword shines lighting the way for your escape.  You find the source of the light a gap in the darkness.  You move through as you fall you here a voice, "You have the power the world is in your hands, but you will not fight alone."  
     You awake in your bed.  Whooo, it was just a dream.  A odd light shines from the other end of the room.  Laying in the cornor is a sword.  The same sword from your dream!!  What does this mean?!

Okay last weekend me and matthew went to Coon Creek.  Total count of people was: from UTM: Me, Matt, Gibson, and Crews, From University of Alabama Some old Paleo guy who was too into Brachs, and 2 female master students you didn't talk very much (one of them Gibson thought was the greatest thing on God's green earth), from University of Georgia was Molly (the prof) I met her at GSA and she remebered me I was shocked, Ryan a undergrad that stayed up till 3am playing Texas Hold Em' with us, a dude that didn't talk much, and some old guy who was quite a bastard.

Friday night me and matt went to Savannah to meet my fam for dinner and then went to pick up groceries fro the four of us through the weekend.  We went back to Coon Creek just in time for Crews to be setting up the telescope.  I've looked through it enough that it isn't any great shakes to me so after Matthew had his fill we went to the research cabin and played yu-gi-oh.  Crews came in after about 30 mins and watched us not much later Gibson came in.  We decided to go to the main building and play hold em.  Ryan joined in and we played hold em till 2am.  Gibson kept wanting to loose so he could take off his cloths so we let him start winning when his pot got small.  After hold em Crews wanted to learn yugioh so me and matthew taught him.  We finally sacked out at 3:30am

Saturday morning I got up at 5:45 to help Gibson with breakfast.  That sucked since I didn't sleep at all!!  And me helping with breakfast turned into me cooking all of it with Crews breezing by and making wise cracks.  Saturday morning was spent at the Parson's Quarry and I got to hear the history of the Devonian again.  At the quarry we ran into the intro paleo class from MTSU.

After the quarry we went to see the Brownsport Fm behind that new high school.  After that we moved toward Clifton to the outcrop Latham is always talking about it started raining so we left there quickly.

We then went to CCSC the other 2 schools hit the creek for collecting, I went to bed.  I got up at 7 just in time for Crews to be dying of hunger.  gibson had left for his daughter's band banquet.  So me, matt, and crews went to Pusser's for food.  We played some new risk game before sacking out at 1am when Gibson got back.  We slept in the research cabin this time.

Sunday we hit some of the outcrops around Selmer.  I was there just to sample on the tree.

The trip was really fun but matthew kept trying to strike out with Gibson though he could only get to strike 1 where as I was sitting on strike 2.8

Weds at about 12:30 Josh decides to go to MTSU's happy hour (Yes all the way in Murfresboro (sp?)).  And of course it was all for a girl (Jennifer).  We leave about 3pm and head down to Parker's Crossroads and catch I-40.  From 40 we travel up till we reached HW-840, which lasted about 10 miles and ended even though we could see the road rolling over hills.  We ended up on HW-100 and jumped onto HW-96 which lead straight to MTSU.  May I add that I the navigator suggested 96 the whole time but the driver vetoed me in favor of 849.  We got to Sante Fe about 6:30 we went in and MTSU jumped up screaming at us coming in.  After the initial shock they ordered us a shot.  There shots were in scotch glasses.

This continues for a while, The other MTSU chick (Catherine I think) kept freakin' staring at me.  At first I thought it was my black eye until i realized she was looking me over not just looking at any one place.  Josh kept telling me she wanted me.  Speaking of that Josh was doing quite well with Jenn at this point.  He had felt up and I must say was playing his cards just right.

Well as Josh was pimping I was stuck between Logan and Bone.  Logan is the MTSU version of Yuko.  Bone is an alcoholic.  So it was either get drunk and ignore the smart boy or talk to the smart boy and not get drunk.  I settled for the later one.  We ended up with 3 shots each and six pictures of beer.  The place closed at 10 and I actually got to hear a last call.

Jenn offered us her apartment for the night ( at that point I knew we werent coming home that night).  Josh continued playing his cards right and seemed to be doing good with jenn.  We were all going to go to Bone's and keep drinking.  We left Josh's truck at Jenn's using his great idea of she had to give us a ride.  

We got to bone's and he showed us his 2000 dollar bed and at this point Josh's night died.  Jenn was laying in the floor with Jonathan and we went in the living room to play video games.  Next thing we knew Jon and Jenn were making out hot and heavy.  Josh was pissed, Me and Greg thought it was hilarious, and Bone was ticked cause they were in his bedroom.  We left with Greg to go get Josh's truck and to go sleep at Greg and Jon's apartment. The whole way Josh couldn't figure out what he did wrong.  

We went to sleep about 3am and got up at 6:45am to come back here.  Poor Josh still couldn't figure it out.  We got back about 10:30 am.  Which gave me just enough time to change shirts and grab my stuff before I headed to class.

It was quite fun and a great road trip even if he didn't get the girl.
